<task id="task_2D9016D8B4E84DBDAF88555E5369546F">
  <title>Set up sub-classifications using the Rule Builder</title>
  <shortdesc>Example steps that describe how you can upload sub-classifications
	 using the Rule Builder. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Analytics" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Admin tools" />
      <othermeta name="subtopic" content="Classifications" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <taskbody>
    <context id="context_92EEC970DE064BE9BDE14C3C939CF724">
      <note>These steps describe how to accomplish the use case described in 
		  <xref href="sub_classification_rule_builder.xml#concept_6C8672C242544D7487E82886BBFABE6E" format="dita" scope="local"><?xm-replace_text Sub-Classifications and the Rule Builder?></xref>.
		  
		</note>
    </context>
    <steps id="steps_15516BC6BC0149248A75C762C66784A5">
      <step id="step_34376036D07C4D19A4E00E051D9D55C7">
        <cmd>Create classifications and sub-classifications in the 
			 <xref href="https://marketing.adobe.com/resources/help/en_US/reference/index.html?f=classifications" format="https" scope="external">Classification Manager</xref>. 
		  </cmd>
        <info>
          <p>Example: 
			 </p>
          <p>
            <image href="graphics/sub_class_create.png" id="image_30AD3968FF8544A088EB1BF70664CC0B">
              <?xm-replace_text Step Info?>
            </image>
          </p>
        </info>
      </step>
      <step id="step_D294F80914014DE7A408A93BCF20546E">
        <cmd>In the 
			 <xref href="classification_rule_builder.xml#concept_C1F219E622044D43852EF5168FF7192A" format="dita" scope="local"><?xm-replace_text Classifications Rule Builder?></xref>,
			 classify the sub-classification key from the original tracking code. 
		  </cmd>
        <info>
          <p>You perform this using a regular expression. In this example, the
				rule to populate 
				<term>Broad Campaign code</term> would use this regular expression:
				
			 </p>
          <table id="table_E3237336C30D4C309504F5239A71DAD7">
            <tgroup cols="5">
              <colspec colname="col01" colnum="1" colwidth="1.00*" />
              <colspec colnum="2" colname="col1" colwidth="4.65*" />
              <colspec colnum="3" colname="col2" colwidth="6.24*" />
              <colspec colnum="4" colname="col3" colwidth="7.86*" />
              <colspec colnum="5" colname="col4" colwidth="6.54*" />
              <thead>
                <row>
                  <entry colname="col01"># 
						</entry>
                  <entry colname="col1">Rule Type 
						</entry>
                  <entry colname="col2">Match 
						</entry>
                  <entry colname="col3">Set Classification 
						</entry>
                  <entry colname="col4">To 
						</entry>
                </row>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <row>
                  <entry colname="col01"></entry>
                  <entry colname="col1">Regular Expression 
						</entry>
                  <entry colname="col2"> [^\:]:([^\:]):([^\:]) 
						</entry>
                  <entry colname="col3">Broad Campaign code 
						</entry>
                  <entry colname="col4">$1 
						</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                  <entry colname="col01"></entry>
                  <entry colname="col1">Regular Expression 
						</entry>
                  <entry colname="col2">[^\:]:([^\:]):([^\:]) 
						</entry>
                  <entry colname="col3">Creative code 
						</entry>
                  <entry colname="col4">$2 
						</entry>
                </row>
              </tbody>
            </tgroup>
          </table>
          <p>
            <note>At this point, you do not populate the sub-classifications 
				  <term>Campaign Type</term> and 
				  <term>Campaign Director</term>. 
				</note>
          </p>
        </info>
      </step>
      <step id="step_0B655BF2E3F44729B10C961893B5BBD4">
        <cmd>Upload a classification file that includes only the
			 sub-classifications specified. 
		  </cmd>
        <info>
          <p>See 
				<xref href="c_multiple-level_classifications.xml#concept_35AD906CDDC4441DAAF70664CF76AA0A" format="dita" scope="local"><?xm-replace_text Multiple-Level Classifications?></xref>.
				
			 </p>
        </info>
        <info>
          <p>Example: 
			 </p>
          <table id="table_AC317A01D16249AFB5E45EAA3951D5B7">
            <tgroup cols="6">
              <colspec colnum="1" colname="col1" colwidth="1.00*" />
              <colspec colnum="2" colname="col2" colwidth="1.35*" />
              <colspec colnum="3" colname="col3" colwidth="2.39*" />
              <colspec colnum="4" colname="col4" colwidth="3.15*" />
              <colspec colnum="5" colname="col5" colwidth="3.04*" />
              <colspec colnum="6" colname="col6" colwidth="1.14*" />
              <thead>
                <row>
                  <entry colname="col1">Key 
						</entry>
                  <entry colname="col2">Channel 
						</entry>
                  <entry colname="col3">Broad Campaign code 
						</entry>
                  <entry colname="col4">Broad Campaign code^Campaign type 
						</entry>
                  <entry colname="col5"> Broad Campaign code^Campaign Director 
						</entry>
                  <entry colname="col6">... 
						</entry>
                </row>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <row>
                  <entry colname="col1">* 
						</entry>
                  <entry colname="col2"></entry>
                  <entry colname="col3">111 
						</entry>
                  <entry colname="col4">Brand 
						</entry>
                  <entry colname="col5">Suzanne 
						</entry>
                  <entry colname="col6"></entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                  <entry colname="col1">* 
						</entry>
                  <entry colname="col2"></entry>
                  <entry colname="col3">222 
						</entry>
                  <entry colname="col4">Brand 
						</entry>
                  <entry colname="col5">Frank 
						</entry>
                  <entry colname="col6"></entry>
                </row>
              </tbody>
            </tgroup>
          </table>
        </info>
      </step>
      <step id="step_70359F422B824EFFBE11AD92FA2C83E7">
        <cmd>To maintain the lookup tables, upload a small file (as shown
			 above). 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult>
          <p>You would upload this file, for example, when a new 
				<term>Broad Campaign code</term> is introduced. This file would
				apply to previously classified values. Likewise, if you create a new
				sub-classification (such as 
				<term>Creative Theme</term> as a sub-classification of 
				<term>Creative code</term>), you upload only the sub-classification
				file, rather than the entire classification file. 
			 </p>
          <p>For reporting these sub-classifications function exactly like
				top-level classifications. This reduces the management burden required to use
				them. 
			 </p>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
    </steps>
  </taskbody>
</task>
